# Week-2-Day-03
python program on strings and operations
# String Operations in Python
# Input string
text = input("Enter a string: ")
# 1. Reverse a String
reversed_string = text[::-1]
print("Reversed String:", reversed_string)

# 2. Check Palindrome
if text == reversed_string:
    print("The string is a Palindrome.")
else:
    print("The string is not a Palindrome.")

# 3. Count Vowels and Consonants
vowels = "aeiouAEIOU"
vowel_count = 0
consonant_count = 0

for char in text:
    if char.isalpha():  # Check if character is alphabet
        if char in vowels:
            vowel_count += 1
        else:
            consonant_count += 1

print("Number of Vowels:", vowel_count)
print("Number of Consonants:", consonant_count)

# 4. Character Frequency
frequency = {}

for char in text:
    if char in frequency:
        frequency[char] += 1
    else:
        frequency[char] = 1

print("Character Frequency:")
for key, value in frequency.items():
    print(key, ":", value)

# 5. String Slicing
print("First 3 characters:", text[:3])
print("Last 3 characters:", text[-3:])
print("String from index 2 to 5:", text[2:6])
print("String with step 2:", text[::2])
